The paper deals with the application of feature visualization techniques to image classification tasks, specifically in the context of white blood cell classification. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a neural network as a feature extractor and the construction of a decision tree based on these features, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of Lucid visualizations for each node in the decision tree, which suggests that it may be relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories, as Lucid is a tool for interpreting and visualizing the inner workings of neural networks.
